      "alert_body": "Fish oil has mild antiplatelet activity. If you have a bleeding disorder, talk to your hematologist before adding fish oil.",
      "alert_headline": "Caution with bleeding disorders",
      "condition_id": "bleeding_disorders",
      "detail": "Omega-3 fatty acids (EPA/DHA) prolong bleeding time by inhibiting thromboxane A2-mediated platelet aggregation and reducing platelet-activating factor. FDA drug labels for icosapent ethyl (Vascepa) and omega-3-acid ethyl esters (Lovaza) explicitly warn about increased bleeding risk. Doses >3g/day have potential antithrombotic effects per FDA labeling.",
